summary:
Gerlo Beernink is a photographer who has been inspired by a variety of topics, always based on what man moves. 
The World Press Photo awarded his report on the miserable psychiatry on the Greek island of Leros.
In addition to documentary photography around work, psychiatry, and archeology, Gerlo has been photographing industrial heritage. His architectural photography has come out of this.
Gerlo is an associated lecturer at the European Center of Emerson College Boston, USA, former teacher at the Fotovakschool, University of Applied Photography.
